distraction: No I was focused on the study
strategies: I did not use specific strategies
familiar: I just tried to think of whether I had heard of the city and then tried to use visual recall if it was seen in phase 1
memorable: Have I heard of this city or not
unique: Was the word more common or unique. More unique are often easier to remember
realistic: Did the word sound strange or use common words
similar: This was the hardest one because I knew there are a lot of random city names. I did it by whether I thought it sounded more like a city name or a streetname.
